{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"93c9c16c-56ff-49a0-ba5e-b64ad050903b","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** – upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n\n2. **Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`** – it's the VSTest entry point and is no longer needed.\n\n3. **Add the new SDK** – install the **`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.NUnit`** package instead.\n\n4. **Enable the platform** – add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** the same way:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n> **Note:** `dotnet test` with `--filter` syntax remains the same, but some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options or custom VSTest extensions may need equivalents under the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"31629567-701d-4475-8c87-e8eb7f5a5c2a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":302},"id":"c414d5d7-e02d-4054-a615-5192d9926d37","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:13.465Z","parentId":"b1eeeab6-a87f-4336-8b6c-0a61418d83f4"}
